{
  "stem": "1895.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 346.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was safe there, because I wasn't registered in the ghetto, and I had no right to be there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if I didn't have a place like this, I would be caught and sent back to the munitions factory for punishment for the escape.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he-- no, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had his family.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His family was survived intact.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were still well to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They still had money.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For some reason, his father had made friends with an influential SS man.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that SS man had warned him continually about ongoing actions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he-- he was able to shelter himself and his family so far.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I became the beneficiary of that, because they would not go to-- into that house to search, because these people were what we considered to be influential.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so I stayed with him until January of '43.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "January of '43, we woke up in the morning, in the dead of winter, [SIGHS] to the screams of [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "By that time, that was a familiar saying.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN] means that it was time for another resettlement or deportation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it's not a translation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN] actually means, 'All Jews out.' But it was the-- that was it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They want all Jews out, because they want to select to see who goes where.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the third deportation began on January 13.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "January 13, they took out about 1,500 people from that small ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that point, perhaps 1,000 were left, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after the third deportation on January 13, which I also witnessed, which I describe in detail in my book.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] After that, I could no longer stay with Moniek and his family, because he told me that they were going to escape to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
